  <body>
    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="background">Global warming is not a myth and will destroy the planet. </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="25" relname="span">

A way to prevent this is to raise petrol prices, 
then people will buy less fuel and become more fuel-efficient. </segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="cause">

Raising petrol prices will make people think before they drive. </segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="19" relname="span">
People will drive less and choose altematives.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="4" relname="result"> 
This would reduce carbon emissions and be cheaper. </segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="20" relname="preparation">
Is driving essential?</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="8" relname="solutionhood">

The planet will die. </segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="20" relname="span">

Increasing petrol prices will help to stop the planet dieing. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="10" relname="motivation">
There are cheap and readily-available alternatives to car travel.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="24" relname="span"> 

Change to a mode of transport that uses less petrol!. </segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="10" relname="motivation">
You will feel better, and your children will live in a better world. </segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="12" relname="concession">
Some car rides are essential. </segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="23" relname="span">

But think before you drive!</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="12" relname="motivation">
You could save money and reduce vour carbon output. </segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="16" relname="evidence">

Petrol isn&apos;t essential to your daily life. </segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="29" relname="span">
Petrol price increases shouldn&apos;t affect you. </segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="18" relname="result">
Reduced petrol use will help save the planet. </segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="28" relname="span">
Petrol prices should be raised</segment>
